Actually I really like the shawl quest...<br>
<br>
If I had one bitch it would be the Tailoring skill being so hard, and being able to fail the tailoring (final) combines.  If they would make all the tailor combines trivial somewhere in the 115-158 range, and make the unable to fail if trivial, the quest would be perfect.<br>
<br>
Tailoring aside, the rest of the risk/reward (or in this quest's case, time/reward) is pretty good.  Fletching - can be 190 in no time, and doesn't take very much pp.  JC - got to 180 in one sitting, cost was a little over 2kpp tho.  Brewing? easy.. Pottery? dead easy.  The mob drops? compared to the rewards, easy stuff... only really bitchy stuff is SG if you don't have a regular group that goes there, and the Royal Blood if you don't have a group you can take there.<br>
<br>
